How does thread safety work in Java?
Thread safety ensures correct results when multiple threads access shared data. It is achieved using synchronization,
locks like ReentrantLock, volatile for visibility, and atomic classes.
===================================
Explain synchronization and types (method, block, static).
“Synchronization is used to ensure that only one thread accesses a critical section at a time to avoid race conditions. 
It is implemented using the synchronized keyword, which uses object-level or class-level locks. 
It can be applied at method level, block level, or static level, with block-level being more efficient.”
===================================
A race condition happens when multiple threads modify shared data concurrently, leading to inconsistent results because the outcome depends on the execution order.
It can be prevented using synchronization or locks.”
eg - 
Think of a bank account:

Balance = 1000
Two threads withdraw 100 at same time

Without synchronization:

Both read 1000
Both update to 900

👉 Final balance = 900 (WRONG)
👉 Correct should be 800

