Difference between fail-fast and fail-safe iterators?
Fail-fast iterators throw a ConcurrentModificationException if the collection is structurally modified during iteration. 
This is because they directly work on the original collection and detect changes using an internal modification count.

Fail-safe iterators, on the other hand, do not throw exceptions because they iterate over a copy or snapshot of the collection, so concurrent modifications do not affect them.”
