What is Spring Boot Auto Configuration?
Auto-configuration works by detecting dependencies on the classpath and automatically configuring required beans using conditional logic.
“Spring Boot auto-configuration automatically configures beans based on the dependencies present in the classpath. It is enabled using @SpringBootApplication,
which includes @EnableAutoConfiguration.

Internally, Spring Boot checks the classpath and uses conditional annotations like @ConditionalOnClass and @ConditionalOnMissingBean to decide which beans to create.

For example, if we include the Spring Web dependency, Spring Boot automatically configures components like DispatcherServlet without manual setup.”
Examples include embedded Tomcat, DataSource, JPA, Jackson for JSON, Spring Security, and Actuator endpoints
Apart from DispatcherServlet, Spring Boot auto-configures many components like embedded Tomcat server, DataSource for database connections, JPA and Hibernate setup, 
JSON conversion using Jackson, Spring Security, Actuator endpoints, and caching. All these are configured automatically based on the dependencies present in the classpath.
