To make a shared counter thread-safe, we can use multiple approaches:

synchronized keyword → ensures only one thread updates at a time
ReentrantLock → more flexible with tryLock and fairness
Atomic classes (AtomicInteger) → best for counters using CAS (non-blocking)
Volatile (only for visibility, not atomicity)

For a counter, I prefer AtomicInteger because it provides better performance.
