In Spring Boot, global exception handling is done using @ControllerAdvice.

We define methods annotated with @ExceptionHandler to handle specific exceptions.

When an exception occurs in any controller, it is intercepted by the global handler and a proper response is returned.

This helps in centralizing error handling and maintaining consistent API responses.
